 ## Process-handover correction ledger
@@
 ### Relationship to uploaded/manual Alfred, Rhythm, Sequencing, Daily, and Craft Flow source materials
 
 Some uploaded source materials in the wider working context describe Alfred, Rhythm, Sequencing, Daily Flows, and Craft Flows. Unless those materials are directly read and recorded in this manifest during a source-extension pass, they remain outside the validated source ledger for canonical doctrine. They may inform operator-local reasoning but must not be claimed as fully read source evidence here.
+
+## Finalization source-extension classes
+
+The final unified diff creation pass classifies finalization inputs without promoting them into permanent doctrine by storage alone.
+
+| Source class | Examples | Finalization use | Doctrine posture |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| Alfred role docs | Alfred managed seed, Alfred GPT/Gem, Alfred use case | Role, boundary, routing, and first-contact alignment basis | Already represented through validated source ledger where read. |
+| Sequencing SSOT update | Sequencing ranked recommendations, templates, instances | Appendix/source-extension context only | Detailed product mechanics remain source-extension dependent unless separately promoted. |
+| Daily Flows / Craft Flows | Daily and craft-flow sequence examples | Evidence for sequence examples and CF-style daily operating context | Not Alfred runtime doctrine by default. |
+| Sequencing science/rationale | Work sprints, interleaving, cognitive modes | Rationale/evidence context | Do not harden as Alfred-owned Algorithm/Sequencing doctrine. |
+| Sequence builder/settings examples | Template and instance examples | Template/context evidence | Detailed implementation deferred. |
+| KB base build index | Source inventory | Coverage/source-status control | Index is source-control input, not doctrine by itself. |
+| Existing appendix source files | Routing, workflow, process handover, Daily Board, Session Export, Pattern Learning | Subordinate detail and retrieval support | Canonical files compact-promote only stable rules. |
+| Temporary proposal/control folders | `appendix_ingestion_handover/`, `cleanup_patch_proposals/` | Current execution and cleanup planning | Cleanup-bound, not doctrine. |
@@
 ## Doctrine-hardening rules
@@
 - **Rule:** Candidate learning is not accepted truth and must route through `LEARNING_QUEUE.md` or the governed promotion path.
+- **Rule:** Temporary proposal/control folders must not be listed as doctrine source. If retained before cleanup, classify them as `TEMP_CONTROL` only.
+- **Rule:** Source/content appendices and temporary process-control artifacts must remain separate in source-status wording.
